main event: A star-like object fell steadily downwards in Humboldt, Saskatchewan, Canada on 27 October 1957.
interesting points: The object was described as bright white and approximately twice the size of a pinhead., The observer first noticed the object at an elevation of 60-70Â°., The object disappeared suddenly to the north after being visible for about 5-10 minutes., The sighting report was not submitted until several years later, in late 1961., Conclusions about the object included possibilities such as a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical phenomenon.
witness description: Gerald W. Kinzel, an officer of the S.P.C.A. Police
